{
  "stem": "27509.1",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I also remember my mother's father, who lived with his son because having had our grandmother with us, Father was-- said no room for more than that.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And that was interesting because my father did not know his father.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "My grandfather-- that's my paternal grandfather-- died at age of 33 of consumption, which was not a rarity in those days.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "It was not a rarity.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So much so that I have got my grandfather's name, which, as you know in Jewish-- in Jewish way, you don't name a child after a living person.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So when I was born, my grandfather was-- not only that I didn't know him, my father didn't remember him.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Because my father was three when-- when his father passed away.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And when my grandmother found herself, you can barely imagine, a-- a woman, whatever she was, at the age of 30 or 28, whatever it is, left with two little children and very little else.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And she had to bring them up on her own in-- and it was quite-- quite an achievement on her part to bring up her two sons.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The older son was a-- a genius class, brilliant mathematician.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "He was a-- a-- an accountant by profession.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And he was so recognized that before the first World War when in Russia proper, or in Moscow in particular, the Jews could not come to live unless they had a special permit for-- for excellence in their profession.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "He had such a permit, and he lived in Moscow serving as a-- an accountant to a firm there.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But most of the time that I remember, he was with us in Bialystok.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "He had his own family, of course.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
